Here are the four files created in `CheckoutWizard/`:

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `Order.cs` | Model classes |
| `CheckoutWizard.razor` | Parent component managing step state and `Order` instance |
| `ShippingStep.razor` | Step 1 — validates Name/Address are non-empty before allowing "Next" |
| `PaymentStep.razor` | Step 2 — "Back" returns to shipping, "Place Order" bubbles the order up |

**Usage example:**

```razor
<CheckoutWizard OnOrderPlaced="HandleOrder" />

@code {
    private void HandleOrder(Order order)
    {
        // process completed order
    }
}
```

The `CheckoutWizard` exposes an `EventCallback<Order> OnOrderPlaced` parameter so the parent receives the completed order when "Place Order" is clicked. The shipping step blocks progression until Name and Address are filled in.
